		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Saint Paul</placeName> <date>October 20 5623</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><sic><addressee>Doctor vice</addressee></sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I am one of them&#44;<lb/> who never read your paper&#44; for this reason&#44; <hi rend="underline">should</hi><lb/> there be any thing <hi rend="underline">worth</hi> of reading&#44; surely&#44; I have<lb/> read it before&#44; and to spend time in reading the ideas<lb/> of your <hi rend="underline">own</hi>&#33; Which is indeed very poor&#44; that would<lb/> be&#44; to waste away time&#44; of which I am able thank God<lb/> to employ it in some thing <hi rend="underline">better</hi> than the fabulous<lb/> paper&#44; as <hi rend="underline">you know me</hi>.  But having been represented<lb/> with one of your scandalous paper&#44; and having observed<lb/> your anxiety to know my where abouts is&#44; and seeing<lb/> that none comply with your wish&#44; I thought it proper<lb/> to inform you myself&#44; and to let you know&#44; that I<lb/> was engaged in this worthy congregation&#44; after your unworthy<lb/> paper was read&#44; to convince you of the truth of the German<lb/> proverb&#44; &#8220;<add>&#63;</add><lb/> <add>&#63;</add>&#8221; Sir&#33;  You say that I am<lb/> <sic>travling</sic> about as a cheat&#44; <sic>As</sic> a convert.  <sic>are</sic> you able sir<lb/> to point out any place where I said that I am so or so&#63;<lb/>  I will consider you one of the two&#59; either as the <persName>king<lb/> Solomon</persName> says <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; or should it be of your own<lb/> fabrication&#44; to injure a person merely because he<lb/> is not of your opinion&#44; you deny the coming of a Messiah<lb/> and I believe in his coming&#44; you deny the <sic>resurection</sic>&#44; and I<lb/> believe it&#44; you say that this is not the same Bible which<lb/> the Almighty gave it to us through <persName>Moses</persName>&#44; and I believe it</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>And above all&#44; in the name of conscience&#44; you know<lb/> me&#44; and all what it was spoken about me&#44; and why<lb/> have you chosen me to be one of your <add>Hebrew</add> to make<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; why have you given me <add>Hebrew</add>&#63;  Why have you<lb/> <sic>deffended</sic> me against the man who spoke ill&#44; of the<lb/> <persName>Rev Mr. Rosenfield</persName>&#44; of yourself and of me&#63;  <sic>indeed</sic><lb/> sir&#44; I see that my opinion of you from the very<lb/> first time I knew you was true&#44; I kept you for an<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; a <add>Hebrew</add>.  It is indeed true the saying of the<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#8212;which in the name of <add>Hebrew</add> says he always<lb/> considered a man by his name&#44; and so I consider<lb/> you&#44; it is not for nothing that your name is vice&#44;<lb/> but because you are the foundation of all viciousness<lb/> since you came to this country the true faith found<lb/> its end&#44; you trod true religion under foot&#44; you made<lb/> <placeName>Israel</placeName> <hi rend="underline">light</hi> <sic>istaed</sic> of Israelite&#44; in short sir you<lb/> are the man who can do good to none&#44; and even to<lb/> yourself without injuring another.  Now sir&#44; I will tell<lb/> you what you are if none told you yet&#44; you are no Talmudist at<lb/> all and your Philosophy indeed while a child I knew it.<lb/>  You can only fool ignorant man&#44; but among learned<lb/> what do you know&#63;  nothing&#8212;know therefore that it is<lb/> this only time I write to answer you&#44; and from now you can<lb/> write whatever you please&#44; no answer will be given to you<lb/> and this time I answer you only that you should not say<lb/> that you silenced me&#44; and to show you that your slandering<lb/> can do me no harm Please God&#44; you have great <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> because you are sure of being engaged for life&#44; and I am sure<lb/> in the help of the true living God of <placeName>Israel</placeName>.  <persName role="author">E. Marcuson</persName>.</p>
